TYPE: Test,
TARGET: control module sensor‑bias / driver return path,
DESCRIPTION: With power off, measure resistance between the sensor‑bias network lower node (the side of the sensor bias resistor that was previously at ~0.12 V) and the main 0 V rail at the control input negative terminal. Then power on and, with reference to battery negative, re‑measure the voltage on that same sensor‑bias lower node and on the relay coil low side while briefly lifting the connection from that node to the relay driver (if separable). Determine whether this node is truly referenced to 0 V through the intended path or is instead connected through an unintended low‑ohmic path into the +12 V network, which would explain the ~0.36 V common‑mode level seen on multiple nodes.,
RESULT: The battery is at 12.0 V relative to its negative terminal, the sensor bias resistor measures nominal 10 kΩ, and its lower node sits at about 0.12 V relative to battery negative while the upper node is at about 11.99 V. The relay coil high side is also at about 11.99 V and its low side is at about 0.36 V relative to battery negative.
